ABAKALIKI – It was a black Sunday for members of the Ebuneagu Vigilante group in Ebonyi State as gunmen shot and beheaded a man said to be a member of the Ebubeagu security operative. The incident was said to have occurred in Ekpelu, in the Ikwo Local Government Area of the state. The slain man has been identified as Sunday Nwafor, 30 years old. Gunmen Enforcing Sit-at-Home Kill APC Youth Leader, One Other In… Sit-At-Home: Gunmen Attack Traders, Burn Vehicle In Enugu The gunmen, numbering about five , were said to have stormed the man’s house at night while he was asleep and shot him dead. They dragged the body out of his room, cut off his head and took it away. The police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in Ebonyi State police command, SP Loveth Odahsaid two suspects had been arrested in connection with the killing. “According to the wife of the deceased who was said to have spoken to policemen, she said that before she heard a gunshot, she over-heard one of the killers telling her husband that he left them in the bush and came back home to enjoy himself by collecting N30,000,” the police spokesperson said. “This is barbaric,” she said. POLL Mrs Odah said the Commissioner of police in the state has ordered an investigation into the incident and vowed to bring to book, those responsible for the act. The Ebubeagu outfit was set up by the Ebonyi State Government to complement the job of the police and other security agencies in checking the crime rates in the state.